= \large \frac{\sin(x+h)}{\cos(x+h)} - \frac{\sin(x)}{\cos(x)}
 = \large \frac{\sin(x+h)\cos(x)-\cos(x+h)\sin(x)}{\cos(x+h)\cos(x)}
 = \large \frac{\sin(x+h-x)}{\cos(x+h)\cos(x)}
