\Rightarrow \large \frac{\tan(x+h) - \tan(x)}{h} = \frac{\sin(h)}{h}[\frac{1}{\cos(x+h)\cos(x)}]
\Rightarrow \large \displaystyle \lim_{h \rightarrow 0} \frac{\tan(x+h) - \tan(x)}{h} = \frac{1}{\cos^{2}(x)} = \sec^{2}(x)
